HEADWORD: Intenible
<hw>In*ten"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + L. <ets>tenere</ets> to hold: cf. L.
<ets>intenibilis</ets> not to be grasped. Cf. <er>Intenable</er>.]</ety>
<def>Incapable of holding or containing.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This captious and <qex>intenible</qex> sieve.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

